Defines the wire-facing shape of a single bubblewrap invocation for ctx-cage: a set of cage-internal path constants and the `BwrapConfig` struct that the sandbox-launching code (elsewhere in `bwrap/`) fills in and consumes to build the `bwrap` argv.

The constants (`CAGE_BIN`, `CAGE_RULES_PATH`, `CAGE_RUN_DIR`, `API_SOCK_NAME`, `CAGE_CLAUDE_CONFIG`, `CAGE_CLAUDE_CRED`, `CAGE_LOCAL_CLAUDE`) are the fixed in-cage paths other modules must bind mounts to match exactly — any code constructing bwrap args or writing synthesized config files must reference these rather than hardcoding strings, or the two will drift. `CAGE_CLAUDE_CRED` and `CAGE_LOCAL_CLAUDE` are rooted at `/tmp` specifically because the cage's `HOME` is set to `/tmp`; changing the cage `HOME` elsewhere breaks these paths silently.

`BwrapConfig` is a plain data holder (`Debug, Clone, Default`) with no validation logic — all invariants are enforced by whatever constructs it. Notable non-obvious fields: `mask_file` must point to an empty *regular* file, not `/dev/null` — bwrap's bind mounts carry `nodev`, so masking a secret with a device node makes every open EACCES and breaks readers (git failing on a masked `.git/config` is the motivating case). `target_root` is bound at the identical host path inside the cage rather than some fixed alias, because compiled build artifacts embed absolute paths and must see the same path both in and outside the cage. `env` is the *entire* cage environment since bwrap is invoked with `--clearenv`, so omitting a variable here means it's unset in the cage, not inherited. `new_session` defaults to `true` for non-interactive safety (blocks TIOCSTI injection) but must be set `false` for interactive Claude Code TUI sessions.